  "description": "Maqam 6 — Nahawand, the Arabic minor, the oldest sleep song. GENDY moves slowly, timeStep minimal, ampStep nearly still. Gravity anchored high so the stochastic voice returns to centre after each wander. Eight breakpoints trace a gentle arc, never a jagged line. This melody has been sung for a thousand years.",
